This paper discusses privacy mechanisms for protecting data in a distributed network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of a real dataset, indicating a focus on data management (cs.DB). The mechanisms described in the paper involve generating noise and preserving accuracy, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions leveraging the law of large numbers, which is a concept in information theory (cs.IT).
